parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the inner primary bearing can cause the clutch to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Knocking or rattling noise coming from the primary case
which houses the clutch and starter.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Wheel Drive Sprocket Bolt Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the bolts holding the rear wheel drive sprocket can cause the wheel to lock up, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: rattling or banging noise from the rear of the bike.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stator rotor cup can cause the stator to come loose, damaging the primary case and potentially leading to a jammed or broken chain, clutch pack, or seized rear wheel, which can result in accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: the clutch pack jams or breaks

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Charging System Failure due to Stator Bolt Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stator bolts can cause the stator to come loose, leading to complete charging system failure, which can leave the rider stranded.
The failure to complete recall repairs can lead to continued risk of stator rotor cup failure, potentially causing accidents or leaving the rider stranded.
symptoms: Dealership fails to complete recall repairs
riders are left with unresolved safety issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose rear sprocket bolts can cause the rear wheel to lock, leading to loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Rattling noise from the rear end of the motorcycle
